@startuml SD15_WebSocket_Notification
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title SD-15: WebSocket Connection + Offline Notification Delivery

actor "User" as U
participant "Astro\nFrontend" as FE
participant "Envoy\nGateway" as GW
participant "Notification\nService\n(Pod A)" as NOTIF_A
participant "Notification\nService\n(Pod B)" as NOTIF_B
database "Redis\n(db3)" as REDIS
database "pg-platform" as DB
queue "Kafka" as KAFKA

== 1. WebSocket Connection on Login ==

U -> FE : Login successful
FE -> GW : WS Upgrade /api/notifications/ws\n+ JWT in query param
GW -> GW : Validate JWT
GW -> NOTIF_A : WebSocket handshake\n(load-balanced to Pod A)
NOTIF_A -> REDIS : SET ws:user123 = pod-A\n(connection registry)
NOTIF_A -> DB : SELECT unread notifications\nWHERE user_id = user123\nAND status = 'unread'
NOTIF_A -> U : Push queued notifications\nvia WebSocket
NOTIF_A --> FE : WS Connected
FE --> U : Notification bell shows\nunread count

== 2. Heartbeat (keep-alive) ==

loop Every 30 seconds
    NOTIF_A -> U : WS Ping
    U -> NOTIF_A : WS Pong
end

== 3. Real-Time Event Arrives ==

KAFKA ->> NOTIF_B : "CommentCreated" event\n(target: user123)
note right of NOTIF_B
    Event lands on Pod B,
    but user's WebSocket
    is on Pod A
end note
NOTIF_B -> REDIS : GET ws:user123
REDIS --> NOTIF_B : pod-A
NOTIF_B -> REDIS : PUBLISH channel:pod-A\n{user123, notification_data}
REDIS ->> NOTIF_A : Subscribe receives message
NOTIF_A -> REDIS : INCR unread:user123
NOTIF_A -> U : WS push\n{type: "reply", message: "..."}
FE --> U : Notification bell updates

== 4. User Goes Offline ==

U -> FE : Close browser tab
FE -> NOTIF_A : WS Disconnect
NOTIF_A -> REDIS : DELETE ws:user123
note right of REDIS : User no longer in registry

KAFKA ->> NOTIF_B : New event for user123
NOTIF_B -> REDIS : GET ws:user123
REDIS --> NOTIF_B : (nil) — user offline
NOTIF_B -> DB : INSERT notification\n(user_id: user123,\nstatus: unread)
note right of DB
    Stored for delivery
    when user reconnects
    (back to step 1)
end note
@enduml
